race.comment: Probably the thinnest race on the card. OXFORD BLUE (7) is second-up and a week between runs. He's always carried a bit of hype but has been costly for punters. But his first-up run was full of merit and this might be the preparation he delivers. He will be hard to beat. STRATUM PRIDE (8) hasn't won out of turn since moving to SA but she's slowly been working her way back to the winner's stall in recent starts. She should get the favours from a low draw and can run a cheeky race with 54kg on her back. The second of the Theodore runners is SAVSONIC (9) and, with 51kg from the inside draw, she can run a knockout race at a big price. Respect FOX GEM (5) and the winning form of IMPOSING SUSPECT (3).
